# Database Migration Safety (Mandatory for Backend DB Changes)

## Backward compatibility

- Prefer additive and backward-compatible schema changes first.
- Avoid destructive changes in the same release where old code may still run.

## Migration standards

- Use clear migration naming with timestamp or ordered sequence.
- Include both forward migration intent and rollback strategy.
- Validate data migrations against expected row counts and constraints.

## Deployment safety

- Apply schema changes in an order that supports zero or low-downtime rollout.
- Gate risky migrations with reviewer approval and deployment notes.

## Neon and connection safety

- PostgreSQL connections must use Neon-compatible SSL settings.
- Never embed database credentials directly in source code.
